Company








Cerahelix designs and manufactures ceramic picofiltration products used for high purity filtration. Our filters meet our customers needs for energy and water conservation and they improve process efficiency for a wide range of industries.

History
Cerahelix was founded in 2011. That same year we were selected as a finalist in the MassChallenge accelerator. We have been awarded $2.5 million in federal SBIR grants from both the National Science Foundation and the Department of Energy to take our technology from proof of concept to working full scale prototype.

Cerahelix has raised $2.9 million in seed stage Angel investment to support early sales of filter elements to prospective customers in each of our key market segments.




Awards and Recognition


Check out Analyst Insights on Lux Populi, naming Cerahelix a high-potential company









 

