Filtration technology for a sustainable future







 


Why settle for plastic?

Introducing:
Ceramic Picofiltration
The Cerahelix PicoHelix filter is made out of renewable ceramic material and is used to make products from biomass, to re-use and recycle resources, and to purify water. The combination of high purity with high durability helps the PicoHelix reduce energy use by more than 90% compared to thermal separation methods. Combined, these features make ceramic picofiltration a leading separation technology for the emerging circular economy. The PicoHelix high purity is achieved by using DNA to form the really small pores in the membrane. Cerahelix is committed to delivering high performing filter products to help our customers meet their sustainability goals.
Interested in the PicoHelix™? Contact us today.


 
 





